com.tsgrp.migration.event

Class RepeatingJDBCQueryListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.event.JDBCQueryListener
        • com.tsgrp.migration.event.RepeatingJDBCQueryListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PostUpdateLogItemEventListener, SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener, TargetEndImportNodeEventListener

    public class RepeatingJDBCQueryListener
extends JDBCQueryListener
    Execute one or more non-binding queries, repeating to allow for repeating attributes in the prepared statement's parameters. For the attributes listed in repeatingAttrNames, construct a "repeating matrix" as shown below: 
     id = 99
 attr1 = [ a, b, c ]
 attr2 = [ g ]
 attr3 = [ s, t ]
    id  attr1  attr2  attr3
 R1 99   a      g      s
 R2 99   b     NULL    t
 R3 99   c     NULL   NULL
    NOTE: This class is JDK 1.4 compatible so that it can be used as-is in projects that cannot use Java 5 or newer (basically, the FileNet projects).

        protected java.lang.Object[] buildQueryParameters(MigrationNode node,
                                                  java.util.List attrNames)
        Build Object[] using the node's values for the attributes specified by JDBCQueryListener.queryAttrNames, using values of JDBCQueryListener.repeatingBehavior and JDBCQueryListener.repeatingDelim to determine how repeating attributes are handled UNLESS the attributes are listed in repeatingAttrNames, in which case additional queries are computed. The Object[] returned is actually an array of Object[], which this class's executeNonBindingQuery will process properly.
